post_text:
Required Face Masks Announcement for Activities
In an effort to prolong fan attendance at our activities, Anamosa Community School District is now requiring the proper wearing of a face mask for all spectators at indoor and outdoor events. The mask must be worn covering both your nose and mouth. It is also expected that spectators maintain a social distance of at least 6 feet between family groups. When eating and/or drinking you may remove your mask, but you need to remain socially distanced from others. Again, we ask for your assistance in prolonging the activity seasons for our students. If you don’t feel you can abide by these requirements, please do not plan to attend school activities. Your cooperation is greatly appreciated! Please share.

post_text: A Big Thank You to Tammy Seeley and the Raider Blue Food Crew! #AnamosaPride
shared_text:
Tammy Seeley is at Anamosa Middle School.
May 20 at 5:11 PM · Anamosa, IA ·

Today was our last door to door delivery for school meals. Since our first delivery on 3/19/20 we have packaged and delivered 50,000 meals! There are so many people to thank I’m not even sure where to begin! But truly I want to say THANK U to all the cooks, bus drivers, paras, school nurses, teachers, janitors, secretaries, student volunteers and administrators that helped to make this possible! Together we did it!!’

June 1st we will begin meal service again with 8 pick up locations. Look for more information on district website and email will come out on Thursday.

post_text: On Thursday, April 2, 2020, Governor Kim Reynolds announced schools would be closed until at least April 30th due to the Covid-19 epidemic. The Anamosa Community School district will participate in the Voluntary Educational Enrichment Continuous Learning Opportunities through the month of April. This means we will not be making up this time outside of the current contracted school year and our district staff will continue to work to support our students in the best, most reasonable ways possible. Our administrative team will be meeting early next week to determine next steps. We will be sharing out more information as it becomes available.

The Anamosa Community School district will participate in the Voluntary Educational Enrichment Continuous Learning Opportunities through the month of April. This means we will not be making up this time outside of the current contracted school year and our district staff will continue to work to support our students in the best, most reasonable ways possible. Our administrative team will be meeting early next week to determine next steps. We will be sharing out more information as it becomes available.

post_text: Anamosa Businesses: I haven't noticed this much in the last several years, but it seems there is a company from La Mesa, CA soliciting businesses for sports posters. The only posters we approve are the ones from the Athletic and Music Boosters. Please do not sign up for anything with them, or any other business except for our boosters. These people get our schedules from the website and take it from there and there is no compensation given to the school. Please support our Boosters when they come around in the summer so they can, in turn, support our kids.

Anamosa Community School District Foundation
December 13, 2019 at 1:05 PM ·

Raider Fans, grab this promotional offer while it last! From today through January 13th, get 6 Raffle Tickets. In addition to getting you in the door, these raffle tickets give you a chance to win one of three cash prizes at the Foundation's largest fundraiser on Saturday, February 8th, 2020. With one of these tickets you will also have an opportunity to play Heads or Tails for a chance at another prize.

You don't need to be present to win! This is an excellent opportunity for parents, grandparents, friends, family and alumni to give back to the school, students and teachers that have and continue to make a difference!

To help spread the excitement and word, simply Like, Share and comment "done" to this post and you will be entered into a drawing for 2 Free Raffle Tickets. That's Like, Share and comment "Done" now GO!

post_text: The Girls JV and Varsity basketball teams will begin their season on Tuesday, Nov 26 at Anamosa High School with a “Girls Night Out” theme. Any girl that attended the summer basketball camp will get in free if they wear their camp t-shirt. The girls will show off drills they learned at camp and participate throughout the evening. Anamosa Dance team will perform. More details to come. Jr. Varsity at 5:30 and Varsity at 7:30. GO RAIDERS.

shared_text:
Heather Bickert Weers
November 15, 2019 at 4:56 PM ·

It was a very cold and emotional end to another Running Club today. We had a kiddo finish that has been with us since kindergarten (that equals 182 miles!!). We had other kids that have been with us since 1st grade. ALL of these kids showed up to complete a marathon (and completed it in the snow). Nic and I aren’t the ones who deserve the thanks, it is the kids who “refuse to be average” and the parents for allowing them to participate and getting them there in the mornings. It’s impossible to describe how proud of EACH kid I am! Love them all!💙

Stephanie Erps is in Anamosa High School.
November 14, 2019 at 11:27 PM · Instagram ·

Laundry Soap Assembly Line today at AHS. We teamed up with United Way, Jones County Family Council, Lutheran Services of Iowa, and other local non profits to make over 500 gallons of laundry soap for those in need in our community. I couldn’t be more impressed with my National Honor Society and Silver Cord kiddos. ❤️❤️❤️ #goraiders #servicelearning #leadership @ Anamosa High School
